gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 110, Bulls 97
gameRecap.excerpt: Joel Embiid (31 points, 15 rebounds, 10 assists) records his 2nd triple-double of the season and 7th of his career as the 76ers defeat the Bulls, 110-97. Tyrese Maxey (21 points, five assists) and Tobias Harris (20 points, eight rebounds) combine for 41 points in the victory, while DeMar DeRozan tallied 16 points for the Bulls in the losing effort. The 76ers improve to 23-10 on the season, while the Bulls fall to 13-20.
